      <hedline>
        <hl1>Oil and Poker</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Arnold Ahlert letter says US release of oil from federal reserves has more to do with politics than prices (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Drop in the Barrel?'', by Paul Krugman (column, Sept. 27): A poker player with a winning hand but not enough money to stay in the game is still a loser. The Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries has much more oil than we do, and has shown a willingness to balance its economic needs against ours. The small release of oil from our reserve has far more to do with politics than prices. That arena, not the market, is where the real ''manipulators'' work.</p>
        <p>ARNOLD AHLERT  Boca Raton, Fla., Sept. 27, 2000</p>
      </block>
